body:
This PR adds a function to diagnose the number concentration of liquid water clouds based on aerosol loading (dust, sea salt and sulfate) and water. The diagnosed number concentration is used to compute the cloud effective radius for radiation. 

The default aerosol and `q_liq` coefficients are all zeros, so when no aerosol is present it should reduce to the currently prescribed number concentration. 

@nefrathenrici -  don't know why, but I was not able to pass the `aerosol_ml_parameters` as a whole struct. I was getting `ERROR: LoadError: ArgumentError: broadcasting over dictionaries and `NamedTuple`s is reserved`. I'm probably creating the parameter struct in Atmos wrong somehow. Maybe you can take a look?
